title: For Sale:  Noveske Recon AR-15 Stainless 16" 1:7" 5.56 223
postcontent:
oveske Recon AR-15 semi automatic rifle chambered for 5.56mm NATO. Noveske is one of the premier manufacturers of AR-15 pattern rifles and this is a perfect example. This rifle features a 16" Stainless Steel barrel with a 1:7" twist rate and Polygonal rifling. Polygonal rifling is an innovative alternative to conventional rifling, boasting increased velocity and accuracy, and significantly easier cleaning. The smooth bore profile provides an improved gas seal, decreases deformation of bullet jackets, and has no sharply angled grooves to hold deposits of fouling. Noveske's Stainless Steel barrels are made to fill a precision role while retaining flawless function. Retaining accuracy and reliability is a complicated balance in that the chamber needs to be slightly modified from the NATO to improve bullet hook-up in the throat, while keeping to functional properties of the NATO body dimensions. The result is a proprietary Noveske chambering. The steel used is a type of 416r and hardened to about 30 HRC prior to any machining. These barrels are button rifled with Noveske's proprietary 7 PT button. This design and the type of stainless used helps the lead edge of the rifling from eroding as fast as it might with conventional rifling, and the barrels tend to outlast others. The barrel has a bead blasted finish for a matte appearance. A mid-length gas system is used, decreasing heat related wear to critical internal componentry, and reducing felt recoil to the operator. For use in any precision application, Noveske recommends a Stainless Steel barrel for its edge in accuracy and excellent reliability.

The upper receiver is a forged Vltor MUR modular design, including an anti-rotation interface with the handguard. The MUR is a rigid Mil Spec design with a flat top Picatinny rail for easy and secure mounting of optics. The walls of the receiver are thicker, making it a stronger, more accurate, and more reliable platform. The MUR is precision milled from forged 7075 aircraft-grade aluminum which has been stress relieved, heat treated, and cryogenically treated. It features extended feed ramps for flawless cycling. The Vltor MUR is likely the highest quality upper receiver available on the market today. The 11" Noveske SWS quad rail handguard is free floated from the barrel to maintain maximum potential accuracy. It is a lightweight design with plenty of space for tactical lights, laser, target designators, bipods, and any other accessories an operator could require. The bolt is is shot peened and Magnetic Particle Inspected to ensure flawlessness, and the bolt carrier has a properly staked gas key. The installed AAC Blackout 51T muzzle device is a clever design that functions as a flash hider and muzzle brake, but also allows rapid installation of compatible sound suppressors. Front and rear BUIS are installed, making this rifle ready to operate.

The lower receiver is a mil spec Noveske Gen II expertly milled from 7075-T6 aircraft-grade aluminum. It has a mil spec black hard coat anodized finish for excellent wear and corrosion resistance. The magazine well is aggressively flared for quick, easy reloads. An ALG Combat Trigger is installed, boasting a smoother, sharper trigger pull by extensive polishing and a Nickel Boron HardLube coating. The geometry of the sear and trigger assembly has not been altered, and thus reliability is not affected. The trigger and hammer are 8620 alloy steel that has been quenched, tempered, and carbuerized, offering very high surface hardness, and the pins are upgraded tempered 4140 Chrome Moly steel with a Nickel-Teflon coating. Pull weight is typically about 6 pounds, making it compliant with U.S. military specifications. A Mil Spec receiver extensions is installed with a Noveske QD plate and Vltor iMod Carbine stock mounted. A popular Magpul MOE pistol grip is equipped and one 30 round PMAG magazine is included.

Caliber: 5.56mm NATO / .223 Remington

Capacity: One 30 round PMAG included

Barrel: 16" 416R Stainless Steel, 1:7" twist polygonal rifled

Dimensions: 33" - 36.25" long

Weight: 7.25 pounds

title: For Sale:  Diamondback DB380MS with Crimson Trace and Extra Magazine - LG-491 DB380
postcontent:
WITH FACTORY UPDATES!                                                                  

I bought this Diamondback DB380MS from Bud's Gun Shop in June 2012.  I installed a Crimson Trace Laser (LG-491) on the pistol in August 2012.  A magazine with a finger extension (DB380 0009-G02) is also included with the pistol, along with the standard magazine the pistol came with.

This model of the DB380 has low profile machined sights and is no longer being sold by Diamondback.  I guess the idea behind the low profile sights is to minimize snags when drawing the weapon.  I find the sights useable, but they are pretty minimal.  I added the laser to compensate for the sights.

It was serviced by the factory because of feeding issues in October 2012. The firearm has all factory updates as of 10/24/12. They replaced the slide, barrel, and trigger mechanism as part of the updates. The Diamondback representative said that they replaced basically everything but the frame.  The Crimson Trace laser was sighted in by Diamondback on 10/24/12.

I have put about 100 rounds through the pistol since the factory updates.  I carry this pistol occasionally, but this pistol shows almost no holster wear.  If you look closely, there is some slight holster wear on the corner of the slide above and to the right side of the muzzle.  Also, I am pretty fanatical about cleaning and lubing my pistols.

The buyer pays for the firearm transfer fee.

After lunch we cover the Law section and finally, we review for the test and take the test. Any missed question will be reviewed and corrected. We give you everything you will need to pass them both during the 8 hour block of instruction course. 
 
The one thing that separates us from others, is we go above and beyond with hands on with your stance and grip of handling your firearm. 
 
We take pride in that after our hands on part, NO ONE has ever failed the qualification!

title: For Sale:  Lee Precision .223 Remington 5.56 Five Die Set 90604 90817 90292
postcontent:
Lee Precision .223 Remington 5.56 Five Die Set 90604 90817 90292.  Price is for ALL 5 DIES.  I will do $140 for these dies and the Lee Classic Cast press I have available separately (see my other listings).

Lee Deluxe 3-Die Set 223 Remington. 

Lee Precision has been producing some of the highest quality reloading equipment for over 50 years. Their Deluxe 3-Die Sets for rifle cartridges are no different. They are made to tight tolerances to help reloaders make consistent and accurate ammunition. These die sets are perfect for both beginning and seasoned reloaders. Each die is made of steel and the set comes with a full length sizing die, collet neck sizing die and bullet seating die. Reloaders use the full length sizing die to produce ammunition to factory-new specifications using new brass or brass cases that were fired in other guns. Full length sizing dies are also great for the reloader who wants to ensure each round loaded will chamber in their rifle with ease. The collet neck sizing die allows reloaders to produce ammunition that has been fire-formed to the chamber of that rifle. Since only the neck is sized more force may be required to get each round to chamber but brass life is extended and a lot of reloaders see an increase in accuracy. This set also includes a bullet seating die, shellholder, powder dipper, storage box and load data.

Technical Information

Dies Included:
Full Length Sizing Die
Collet Neck Sizing Die
Bullet Seating Die

Die Size: Standard 7/8"-14 threads
Shellholder Required: YES
Shellholder Included: Yes
Notes:
Accessories Included:
Powder Dipper
Storage Box
Load Data

Lee Factory Crimp Die 223 Remington

The Lee Precision Factory Crimp Die is designed to give reloaders the perfect crimp on each round of reloaded ammunition. The Factory Crimp Die crimps the bullet more firmly in place than any other die with more uniform pressure. The Factory Crimp Die features a collet that squeezes the case mouth into the crimping groove for a firm hold. It is nearly impossible to buckle the case when crimping when compared to a regular roll crimp die. Lee's testing has shown that using a Factory Crimp Die provides a more uniform pressure curve, increasing the accuracy of any bullet. Shellholder sold separately.

Technical Information

Material: Steel
Fits: Reloading presses that accept standard 7/8"-14 Threads
Accessories:
Plastic Storage Box

Lee Universal Depriming and Decapping Die

The Lee Universal Decapping and Depriming Die is made of steel and allows the reloader to take cases directly from the range and decap them without the need of lube or cleaning. The Decapper is guaranteed unbreakable by Lee and even removes crimped in primers and accepts cases up to .550 in diameter. Shellholders sold separately. Comes in a plastic case. While this is listed as a Universal die, it is not recommended for use with 17 or 20 caliber cases.
Technical Information

Size: Standard 7/8"-14 threaded die
Notes:
Works with cases with a diameter up to .550" in diameter
Not recommended for 17 or 20 caliber cases
